        public PagedList<String> listDatabasesPaged(Integer maxResults,
                                            String pageToken,
                                            String databaseNamePattern)
        Description copied from interface: Catalog
        Get paged list names of all databases in this catalog.
        Specified by:
        listDatabasesPaged in interface Catalog
        Parameters:
        maxResults - Optional parameter indicating the maximum number of results to include in the result. If maxResults is not specified or set to 0, will return the default number of max results.
        pageToken - Optional parameter indicating the next page token allows list to be start from a specific point.
        databaseNamePattern - A sql LIKE pattern (%) for database names. All databases will be returned * if not set or empty. Currently, only prefix matching is supported.
        Returns:
        a list of the names of databases with provided page size in this catalog and next page token, or a list of the names of all databases if the catalog does not Catalog.supportsListObjectsPaged().

      • loadSnapshot

        public Optional<Snapshot> loadSnapshot(Identifier identifier,
                                       String version)
                                throws Catalog.TableNotExistException
        Description copied from interface: Catalog
        Return the snapshot of table for given version. Version parsing order is:
        • 1. If it is 'EARLIEST', get the earliest snapshot.
        • 2. If it is 'LATEST', get the latest snapshot.
        • 3. If it is a number, get snapshot by snapshot id.
        • 4. Else try to get snapshot from Tag name.
        Specified by:
        loadSnapshot in interface Catalog
        Parameters:
        identifier - Path of the table
        version - version to snapshot
        Returns:
        The requested snapshot
        Throws:
        Catalog.TableNotExistException - if the target does not exist

      • listViewsPaged

        public PagedList<String> listViewsPaged(String databaseName,
                                        Integer maxResults,
                                        String pageToken,
                                        String tableNamePattern)
                                 throws Catalog.DatabaseNotExistException
        Description copied from interface: Catalog
        Get paged list names of views under this database. An empty list is returned if none view exists.
        Specified by:
        listViewsPaged in interface Catalog
        Parameters:
        databaseName - Name of the database to list views.
        maxResults - Optional parameter indicating the maximum number of results to include in the result. If maxResults is not specified or set to 0, will return the default number of max results.
        pageToken - Optional parameter indicating the next page token allows list to be start from a specific point.
        tableNamePattern - A sql LIKE pattern (%) for view names. All views will be returned if not set or empty. Currently, only prefix matching is supported.
        Returns:
        a list of the names of views with provided page size in this database and next page token, or a list of the names of all views in this database if the catalog does not Catalog.supportsListObjectsPaged().
        Throws:
        Catalog.DatabaseNotExistException - if the database does not exist
